        "content": "<p>A few hours ago I made <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/pull/5147\">lean4#5147</a> which:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>adds <code>@[elab_as_elim]</code> to <code>Quot.rec</code> and <code>Nat.(case)strongInductionOn</code>. The first addition is a TODO in <code>Mathlib.Init.Quot</code></li>\n<li>based on a suggestion from <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"387244\">@Yaël Dillies</span>, renames <code>Nat.(case)strongInductionOn</code> to <code>Nat.(case)strongRecOn</code></li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 464845117,
        "sender_full_name": "Jeremy Tan",
        "timestamp": 1724505048
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>However <code>Nat.strongRecOn</code> is a Batteries definition. What should we do with it?</p>",
